<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>DropDown Menu</h2>
        <p>
            Change a basic Menu into an expandable dropdown menu with the Dropdown Menu plugin.
        </p>
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Horizontal</h2>
        <p>
            Dropdown menus build on the <NavLink href="menu">Menu</NavLink> component's syntax.Use the tag of  <code>MenuDropdown</code>
            to the menu container to set up the dropdown.
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
                     Content="PE1lbnVEcm9wZG93bj4KICAgIDxsaT48TmF2TGluayBocmVmPSIjIj5JdGVtIDE8L05hdkxpbms+PC9saT4KICAgIDxsaT48TmF2TGluayBocmVmPSIjIj5JdGVtIDI8L05hdkxpbms+PC9saT4KICAgIDxsaT48TmF2TGluayBocmVmPSIjIj5JdGVtIDM8L05hdkxpbms+PC9saT4KICAgIDxsaT48TmF2TGluayBocmVmPSIjIj5JdGVtIDQ8L05hdkxpbms+PC9saT4KPC9NZW51RHJvcGRvd24+" />
        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuDropdown>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1</NavLink></li>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 2</NavLink></li>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 3</NavLink></li>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 4</NavLink></li>
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuDropdown>
        <p>
            To create dropdown menus, nest a new <Code>@("<MenuTopLevel>")</Code>inside an <Code>@("<li>")</Code>.
            You can nest further to create more levels of dropdowns.
        </p>

        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout TypeClass="primary">
            Note that the <Code>@("<MenuTopLevel>")</Code> goes after the <Code>@("<NavLink>")</Code>, and not inside of it.
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
                     Content="" />
        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuDropdown>
            <li>
                <NavLink href="#">Item 1</NavLink>
                <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1A</NavLink></li>
                    <li>
                        <NavLink href="#">Item 1B</NavLink>
                        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1B i</NavLink></li>
                            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1B ii</NavLink></li>
                            <li>
                                <NavLink href="#">Item 1B iii</NavLink>
                                <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1B iii alpha</NavLink></li>
                                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1B iii omega</NavLink></li>
                                </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <NavLink href="#">Item 1B iv</NavLink>
                                <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1B iv alpha</NavLink></li>
                                </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                            </li>
                        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                    </li>
                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 1C</NavLink></li>
                </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
            </li>
            <li>
                <NavLink>Item 2</NavLink>
                <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 2A</NavLink></li>
                    <li><NavLink href="#">Item 2B</NavLink></li>
                </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuTopLevel>
            </li>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 3</NavLink></li>
            <li><NavLink href="#">Item 4</NavLink></li>
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Navigation.MenuDropdown>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Vertical</h2>
        <p>
            add the attribute <Code>Vertical</Code> set it in <Code>true</Code> to the top-level menu to make it vertical. Sub-menus are automatically vertical,
            regardless of the orientation of the top-level menu.
        </p>
        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout TypeClass="primary">
            <p>
                Menus are block-level elements, which means they stretch to fill the width of their container. To make the below
                example less goofy, we've hard-coded a <Code>max-width</Code> on the menu.
            </p>
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout>

        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderTitle="Razor" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90"
